<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="338" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,489,1107]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,489,515]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Remarks</emphasis>
. The status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1978" box="[427,555,490,515]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bodotriidae" genus="Iphinoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[427,555,490,515]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">I. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was clarified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Corbera" box="[751,923,489,515]" firstAuthor="Corbera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref17646" refString="Corbera, J. (1994) A new record of Iphinoe crassipes Hansen, 1895 (Cumacea, Bodotriidae) from Catalonian coast (NE Spain). Scientia Marina, 58 (3), 272 - 276." type="journal article" year="1994">Corbera (1994)</bibRefCitation>
who presented a new description of the adult male. Previous descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hansen 1895)" baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[502,806,524,551]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bodotriidae" genus="Iphinoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[502,631,526,551]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">I. crassipes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen" box="[647,798,524,551]" firstAuthor="Hansen" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref19563" refString="Hansen, H. J. (1895) Ordnung: Cumacea. In: Isopoden, Cumaceen und Stomatopoden der Plankton Expedition N Atlantic. Ergebnisse der Atlantic Ocean Plankton. Expedition, 2, 1 - 105. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10413" type="journal article" year="1895">Hansen 1895</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bacescu 1961)" baseAuthorityName="Bacescu" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[863,1254,525,552]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bodotriidae" genus="Iphinoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="crassipes" subSpecies="haifae">
<emphasis box="[863,1070,525,551]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">I. crassipes haifae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bacescu" box="[1086,1246,525,552]" firstAuthor="Bacescu" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="495 - 502" refId="ref16881" refString="Bacescu, M. (1961) Contribution a l'etude des Cumaces de la Mediterranee et particulierement des cotes d'Istrael. Rapport et proces-verbaux de reunions C. I. E. S. M., 16 (2), 495 - 502." type="journal article" year="1961">Băcescu 1961</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
had been based on preadult males. The species differs from other Mediterranean congenerics in that it has two terminal aesthetascs on antenna 1. Moreover, the dorsal carina is unarmed in males (
<bibRefCitation author="Corbera" box="[879,1037,594,620]" firstAuthor="Corbera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref17646" refString="Corbera, J. (1994) A new record of Iphinoe crassipes Hansen, 1895 (Cumacea, Bodotriidae) from Catalonian coast (NE Spain). Scientia Marina, 58 (3), 272 - 276." type="journal article" year="1994">Corbera 1994</bibRefCitation>
) and the CL/CD ratio is about 1.5. Morphological data on female specimens are not available. A truncated pseudorostrum and a pair of lateral carinae are further diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[548,676,664,689]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bodotriidae" genus="Iphinoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[548,676,664,689]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">I. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="338" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,489,1107]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,493,697,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[506,702,698,724]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bodotriidae" genus="Iphinoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[506,702,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Iphinoe crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sensu lato) is present in the western Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Corbera" firstAuthor="Corbera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref17646" refString="Corbera, J. (1994) A new record of Iphinoe crassipes Hansen, 1895 (Cumacea, Bodotriidae) from Catalonian coast (NE Spain). Scientia Marina, 58 (3), 272 - 276." type="journal article" year="1994">Corbera 1994</bibRefCitation>
) and in the Levantine sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Bacescu" box="[502,663,733,760]" firstAuthor="Bacescu" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="164 - 171" refId="ref16927" refString="Bacescu, M. (1969) Deux cumaces nouveaux: Diastyloides carpinei n. sp. dans la Mediterranee Hemilamprops lotusae dans l'Atlantique Argentin. Revue Roumanie de Biologie Academiei Republicii Socialiste Romania, 1969, 164 - 171." type="journal article" year="1969">Bâcescu 1969</bibRefCitation>
). Its distribution is typical of a circumtropical species 
<bibRefCitation author="Corbera" box="[1259,1431,733,759]" firstAuthor="Corbera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref17646" refString="Corbera, J. (1994) A new record of Iphinoe crassipes Hansen, 1895 (Cumacea, Bodotriidae) from Catalonian coast (NE Spain). Scientia Marina, 58 (3), 272 - 276." type="journal article" year="1994">Corbera (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Bacescu" box="[259,436,767,794]" firstAuthor="Bacescu" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="495 - 502" refId="ref16881" refString="Bacescu, M. (1961) Contribution a l'etude des Cumaces de la Mediterranee et particulierement des cotes d'Istrael. Rapport et proces-verbaux de reunions C. I. E. S. M., 16 (2), 495 - 502." type="journal article" year="1961">Băcescu (1961)</bibRefCitation>
explained the record of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bacescu" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[721,930,768,794]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bodotriidae" genus="Iphinoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="crassipes" subSpecies="haifae">
<emphasis box="[721,930,768,794]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">I. crassipes haifae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1047,1109,768,794]" name="Israel" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Israel</collectingCountry>
coast as a possible invasion through the Suez Canal.At first 
<bibRefCitation author="Corbera" box="[506,677,802,828]" firstAuthor="Corbera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref17646" refString="Corbera, J. (1994) A new record of Iphinoe crassipes Hansen, 1895 (Cumacea, Bodotriidae) from Catalonian coast (NE Spain). Scientia Marina, 58 (3), 272 - 276." type="journal article" year="1994">Corbera (1994)</bibRefCitation>
casted doubt on this hypothesis, based on the occurrence of this species off the northeastern coast of the Iberian Peninsula (Catalogna coast). However, after a finding in a new western Mediterranean locality (along Valenciana coast) 
<bibRefCitation author="Corbera" box="[695,867,871,898]" firstAuthor="Corbera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref18321" refString="Corbera, J. (2015) Orden Cumacea. Revista IDE @ - SEA, 76, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="2015">Corbera (2015)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that this disjunct distribution could be a shipping introduction way.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,489,1107]" box="[199,1225,941,967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">The species has never been reported from the Italian coast, nor was it found in our samples.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,489,1107]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">
<bibRefCitation author="Corbera" box="[199,370,976,1002]" firstAuthor="Corbera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref17646" refString="Corbera, J. (1994) A new record of Iphinoe crassipes Hansen, 1895 (Cumacea, Bodotriidae) from Catalonian coast (NE Spain). Scientia Marina, 58 (3), 272 - 276." type="journal article" year="1994">Corbera (1994)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the ecology of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[652,848,976,1002]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bodotriidae" genus="Iphinoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[652,848,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Iphinoe crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[864,977,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">sensu lato</emphasis>
), reporting that the species lives in warm temperate waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen" box="[358,511,1009,1036]" firstAuthor="Hansen" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref19563" refString="Hansen, H. J. (1895) Ordnung: Cumacea. In: Isopoden, Cumaceen und Stomatopoden der Plankton Expedition N Atlantic. Ergebnisse der Atlantic Ocean Plankton. Expedition, 2, 1 - 105. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10413" type="journal article" year="1895">Hansen 1895</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones" box="[522,651,1009,1037]" firstAuthor="Jones" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="183 - 212" refId="ref19357" refString="Jones, N. S. (1956) Cumacea from the West Coast of Africa. Atlantide Report, No. 4, 183 - 212." type="book chapter" year="1956">Jones 1956</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Le Loeuff &amp; Intes" box="[663,935,1010,1037]" firstAuthor="Le Loeuff" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="19 - 46" refId="ref20090" refString="Le Loeuff, P. &amp; Intes, A. (1972) Les Cumaces du plateau continental de Cote d'Ivoire. Cahiers Or. S. T. O. M., Series Oceanographique, 10 (1), 19 - 46." type="journal article" year="1972">Le Loeuff &amp; Intes 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Day" box="[947,1059,1010,1037]" firstAuthor="Day" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="159 - 290" refId="ref18570" refString="Day, J. (1978) Southern African Cumacea, Part 2: Family Bodotriidae, subfam. Bodotriinae. Annals South African Museum, 75 (7), 159 - 290." type="journal article" year="1978">Day 1978</bibRefCitation>
) such as the western coast of Africa, and avoids the cold upwelling zones (
<collectingCountry box="[632,777,1045,1071]" name="South Africa" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[832,955,1045,1071]" name="Mauritania" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Mauritania</collectingCountry>
coasts). 
<bibRefCitation author="Corbera" box="[1055,1227,1045,1071]" firstAuthor="Corbera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref17646" refString="Corbera, J. (1994) A new record of Iphinoe crassipes Hansen, 1895 (Cumacea, Bodotriidae) from Catalonian coast (NE Spain). Scientia Marina, 58 (3), 272 - 276." type="journal article" year="1994">Corbera (1994)</bibRefCitation>
found this species in sandy bottoms at a depth of 
<specimenCount box="[496,559,1080,1107]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" type="generic">
<quantity box="[496,553,1080,1107]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" unit="m" value="15.0">15 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
